DialogueNode.dialogue: Hey Janet, do you have a minute?
Not really but I'm guessing I don't really have a choice, haha. What's up Alex?
A lot, actually. As you know, I'm still looking into that report of sexual discrimination...
Alex, I told you, I don’t know anything and I’m not gonna talk about this anymore.
If you need me to confirm or deny specific information, I'd consider doing so, but otherwise, ask someone else. I'm not gonna offer up any additional information.

(If talked to Dave) Janet, I have already talked to Dave who has confirmed that Stan inappropriately and publicly called out Sharon, and I know you were at that meeting. Are you sure you can't elaborate?
(Available whether or not you talked to Dave) Come on, Janet. You must know something. I'm sure you've experienced this firsthand. Isn't there anything you can tell me?
(If didn't talk to Dave yet) Alright, I'll come back when I have more concrete evidence, then.
Thanks for understanding, Alex. That means a lot to me.
Alex, I'm not comfortable with this. I'm not risking my job over this. Goodbye.
Alright, fine. Yes, Stan yelled at Sharon, but that's all I'm going to say about this. I don't want to risk my job here, Alex. Please understand that.
